<Layout title="Biography">
    <main>
        <HeroBanner
            title="Biography"
            description="It's just a way of life, lived from the heart. We dont see colour or difference, we just see one world - (Ras Jahknow Brimbank Weekly)"
            image="/carousel-1.jpeg"
        />
        <section class="w-8/12 container mx-auto my-10 flex justify-between">
            <div class="w-6/12"></div>
            <div class="w-6/12">
                Ras Jahknow blazes new soul and fresh rhythms into what is
                described best as culturally rich, roots reggae music.
                Passionate vocals in English and Creole weave through the
                diverse native sounds from the African island nation of Cape
                Verde, Brazil, Tanzania and Mauritius to Australia. The band
                embodies a vision of unity, respect and peace, built on the
                foundation of irresistible, reggae rhythms. Cape Verdean born
                Ras Jahknow formed the band in late 2010, and they have since
                cemented themselves as one of Melbourne’s most iconic reggae
                ensembles, showcasing at 2014 Antenna Awards and performing at
                numerous festivals such as: Brimbank Festival – 2011 Black
                Harmony Gathering – 2012 The West African Festival – Immigration
                Museum Emerge Festival – 2012 Rise Festival – Federation Square
                – 2012 Viva Victoria Festival – 2014 Waitangi Festival – 2014
                French Fest – 2014 Bob Marley Birthday Bash – Corner Hotel –
                2012, 2013, 2015, 2016, 2017 & 2018 Africa Music & Cultural
                Festival – 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018 Africultures Festival –
                Sydney – 2016 Strawberry Fields Festival – 2015 Tanglewood
                Festival – 2015, 2016 & 2017 Jamaican Music & Food Festival –
                2016, 2017, 2018 St Kilda Festival – 2017 Brunswick Music
                Festival – 2017 Sunraysia Multicultural Festival – 2017 Roots
                Reggae Cruise around Melbourne - 2017 Live n Local Winter Music
                Festival - 2017 Bali Reggae Star Festival - 2017 Langkawi Island
                International Music Festival - 2017 Samba Reggae Carnivale 2017
                & 2018 Moomba Festival 2019 Indonesia 2019 Festival Da Gamboa
                2019 (Cape Verde) Lisbon 2019 Ras Jahknow has spent time in
                numerous countries abroad, developing a rounded, cultural
                understanding, and through the Ras Jahknow Band, he aims to
                bridge the contemporary gaps in cultural understanding and
                unity. Ras Jahknow Band released their debut album “Jah Sta Li”
                in May 2014, followed by a dub remix released later the same
                year. Both records were produced by acclaimed personality Wayne
                ‘Lotek’ Bennett at Counter Clockwise Studios. Current releases
                have enjoyed airplay across national radio such as Triple J and
                hundreds of Community radio stations both nationally and abroad.
                2015 saw the band release a film clip for ‘Jah Sta Li’,
                embarking on a the Victorian ‘Jah Live’ tour to celebrate the
                single’s success. In mid 2015, Ras Jahknow was nominated for a
                Music Victoria Genre Award for ‘Best Global & Reggae Album’. In
                2017, Ras Jahknow humbly accepted the Award for Best Reggae
                Performer/Band of the year 2015/16 at the Australia Reggae Radio
                Music Awards. Afroshine Australia Awards - Excellence Artistic
                Talents (Music/Reggae) 2018 Ras Jahknow was nominated for a
                Music Victoria Genre Award for ‘Best Reggae and Dancehall Act)
                2018 Ras Jahknow received an Award of excellence for support the
                Community Talents 2019 (ACTap) ‘Jah Sta Li’ is available for
                download on iTunes and all major digital online outlets. ‘Jah
                Sta Li Dub’ is now available via Bandcamp. The organic sound is
                a product of the many talented musicians who have music and
                performance in their blood. All members are
                multi-instrumentalists and come from professionally skilled
                music backgrounds. Ras Jahknow has released six stellar singles
                ‘You &I;’ in 2011 and ‘Get up & Live’ Feat. Jason Heerah in
                2012, ‘Can’t Change Jah Jah Man’, ‘Let’s Unite’ 2013, ‘Erba
                Internacional’ in 2014, ‘What A Gwan’ 2016, all having regular
                airplay on local and international radios. Ras Jahknow’s Album
                ‘JAH STA LI’ & ‘JAH STA LI’ Dub Album are both available now.
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
